verses.roman:
guṇārṇava miśra nāme eka vipra ārya
śrī-mūrti-nikaṭe teṅho kare sevā-kārya

synonyms: guṇārṇava miśra—of Guṇārṇava Miśra; nāme—by the name; eka—one; vipra—brāhmaṇa; ārya—very respectable; śrī-mūrti-nikaṭe—by the side of the Deity; teṅho—he; kare—does; sevā-kārya—activities in devotion.
translation: One respectable brāhmaṇa named Śrī Guṇārṇava Miśra was serving the Deity.
